    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Branch of forestry concerned with the overall administrative, economic, legal and social matters regarding the protection and regulation of forests for wildlife, recreation, aesthetics, preventing fire, and harvesting of wood products, with the aim of balancing conservation and economics.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
